{
  "$comment": "Palette-gate contract for the Bounded Systems brand tokens. Declares EVERY real foreground/background pairing the semantic tokens are designed for, plus the categorical status set. The gate (vendor/conformance-kit/gates/palette-gate.mjs) resolves fg/bg against the generated tokens.css and FAILS CLOSED on any WCAG-AA, CVD-safe (deuteranopia/protanopia/tritanopia), APCA, or non-text (WCAG 1.4.11) violation. NO decorative exemptions: hairlines/dividers are declared as `ui` and must clear 3:1.",
  "$apca": "kind=text uses the gate's APCA floor (minLcText, 60). The PRIMARY BODY pairings additionally declare size/weight, which invokes the gate's size-aware APCA COMFORT tier (Lc>=90 at 16px) — the body type was bumped 15px->16px precisely so primary body clears comfort, not just WCAG-2 AA. Secondary/label/accent roles are held to the APCA baseline floor (Lc>=60), which they clear.",
  "thresholds": {
    "minRatioText": 4.5,
    "minRatioLarge": 3.0,
    "minRatioUi": 3.0,
    "minLcText": 60,
    "minLcLarge": 45,
    "collapseDeltaE": 10
  },
